profile.primary_concern: fear of discrimination and stigma from healthcare providers

context: As a young woman living with HIV-related stigma, you often feel anxious about seeking medical help. Your fear of being judged or mistreated because of your status creates significant barriers to accessing PrEP. You are hopeful that PrEP could offer additional protection, but the emotional weight of stigma weighs heavily on your mind.
